09/04/2003
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- The EU may grant $1 billion to Turkey over the next three years to help it prepare for accession to the Union, according to a draft of the joint declaration prepared at the Turkey-EU Joint Consultative Committee meeting. The two-day meeting began on Monday (7 April) in Istanbul. The declaration notes that"if Turkey fulfils the Copenhagen political criteria, the EU will open negotiations with Turkey without delay."
Meanwhile, the Group of Seven leading industrialised countries (G7) issued a statement Tuesday, congratulating Turkey for signing a pledge to follow reform recommendations by the IMF. (Anadolu Agency, Turkish Daily News, AFP - 08/04/03)
